channel.title: How do I delete an object
channel.description: Ok, there's a glitch in my server where you click on the chest in the party room and u get 99 all stats, and 2147b d chains....How do i delete the chest?

item.title: How do I delete an object
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

Btw, i forgot to add that the place to delete the object is in

public void Deleteobjects() {

And it works like this:

deletethatobject(X, Y); //Nameofobject

X= X coord
Y= Y Coord
Nameofobject= Name of the object

And if you want to delete walls or gates use

public void Deletewalls() {

(That was just a fast add-on from my last post.)

or search for the coords it is at, and then delete that. It might be in objects.cfg

That isnt the right way, because that item was never added to the newobjects void (Ive tested on project czar once)

You have to use deleteobject (search for it in client.java)

Its same as makeglobalobject

xcept it deletes it after u type x coord of object y coord, and object id
